headline: Trump strikes trade deal with Vietnam, imposes 20% tariff
summary: Investing.com -- U.S. President Donald Trump announced Wednesday that he has reached a trade agreement with Vietnam, becoming the third such deal following earlier agreements with the UK and China ahead of a July 9 deadline.

headline: Nike stock pops after Trump says US reaches trade deal with Vietnam
summary: Nike stock rose Wednesday after Trump said the US had struck a trade deal with Vietnam, a key import source for the company and others in the footwear industry.

headline: Goldman cautious on mid cap athleisure, starts Crocs, Deckers at Sell
summary: Investing.com -- Goldman Sachs began coverage of mid‑cap U.S. athleisure names with a cautious stance, arguing that stiffer competition and fickle consumer demand will separate winners from laggards in the crowded footwear and sportswear arena.

headline: These 3 Stocks Have Been the Worst Performers in the S&P 500 This Year. Have They Bottomed Out?
summary: The S&P 500 has recovered from a tough start to 2025, but the stocks listed here are all down more than 35%.  Many stocks are now trading near their all-time highs, and so is the S&P 500, which is up around 5.5% through the first six months of the year.  The three biggest losers in the index at the halfway point of the year are Deckers Outdoor (NYSE: DECK), Enphase Energy (NASDAQ: ENPH), and UnitedHealth Group (NYSE: UNH).
